{
  "texts": [
    "The logic behind this approach was similar to representational similarity analysis, or \"RSA\" (Kriegeskorte et al., 2008).",
    "First, I constructed a correlation matrix between all nine dimensions using the human norms (see Fig. 5a).",
    "This reveals which psycholinguistic dimensions are positively correlated (e.g., imageability and concreteness) and which are negatively correlated (e.g., age of acquisition and familiarity), and to what degree.",
    "I then constructed an analogous matrix using the LLM-generated norms for each dimension (see Fig. 5b).",
    "12 The primary reason for running a z-test here, rather than a t test, was based on the precedent from past work (Clogg et al., 1995)."
  ]
}